<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,432,601]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,432,457]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
External margin of eyes at the same level as the pronotum lateral margin. Rostrum not reaching the segment IV of abdomen. Hemelytra covered by woolly or silky pubescence; cuneus not reaching apex of the membrane. Pygophore of males without projection on the left side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
